d through stellar winds,\nrather than eruptions. From the ALMA and VISIR non-detections, plus the derived\nextinction map, we deduce that the infrared emission observed by space\ntelescopes must arise from extended, diffuse dust within the ionised region.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Nov 2016 12:58:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 23 Dec 2016 13:03:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-26"}
